<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause id="_8bf4adbc-65e9-4015-b56e-16f9e24400cd" outputclass="ncc-clause"><meta><facet building="Class 2"/><facet building="Class 3"/><facet building="Class 4"/><facet building="Class 5"/><facet building="Class 6"/><facet building="Class 7a"/><facet building="Class 7b"/><facet building="Class 8"/><facet building="Class 9a"/><facet building="Class 9b"/><facet building="Class 9c"/><facet building="Class 10b"/><facet building="Class 10c"/></meta><sptc>H7F4</sptc><title id="_28467708-022a-43c6-a441-8c6da1144bee">Bushfire areas</title><archive-num>2019: F2.7.4</archive-num><subclause id="_be43700d-351a-44c9-b1f7-ef71df2bd283" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_e117a888-45a9-4bf8-bef3-45eda21c7349">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>A Class 1 building or a Class 10a building or deck associated with a Class 1 building constructed in a <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/1243_0.7.0.xml#_2c223137-7ce5-4993-bd69-503e243c9453" id="_cc707ac0-a897-41ff-967c-3f2b39ac23fa" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">designated bushfire prone area</xref> is to provide resistance to bushfires in order to reduce the danger to life and reduce the risk of the loss of the building.</p></subclause></clause>